doc.ContractDescription: THIS PROPOSAL COVERS THE ACTIVITIES OF THE PENN STATE GROUP ON THE BACCUS HIGH-ALTITUDE BALLOON EXPERIMENT IN ANTARCTICA AND ON THE CREAM MISSION TO THE ISS. THESE PROJECTS TOGETHER WILL ACHIEVE DEFINITIVE MEASUREMENTS OF THE COSMIC-RAY ELEMENTAL SPECTRA INTO THE PEV RANGE (NUCLEI) AND OF COSMIC-RAY ELECTRONS INTO THE TEV RANGE, AS WELL AS DETAILED STUDIES OF SECONDARY NUCLEI (SUCH AS B OR THE SUB- FE ELEMENTS). THESE ARE THE EXPERIMENTAL MEASUREMENTS NEEDED TO SORT OUT THE DETAILS OF COSMIC-RAY ACCELERATION AND PROPAGATION IN THE GALAXY, A LONG STANDING PUZZLE IN PARTICLE ASTROPHYSICS.
